msgid "Become invincible when entering a stage."
msgstr "Дає недоторканість після переходу на новий етап."

#: .strings.SS2_ITEM_PORTABLEREACTOR_LORE
msgid ""
"Eighty seconds. Damned lizards. They're more cunning than they seemed.\n"
"\n"
"Seventy seconds. She took a moment to breathe. What had once been harsh "
"winds was no still air, contained within the miniature biosphere.\n"
"\n"
"Sixty seconds. She counted her bullets.\n"
"\n"
"Fifty seconds. Two remaining magazines, a box-worth of shells, one grenade - "
"waterlogged, and a duled knife. Not nearly enough.\n"
"\n"
"Forty seconds. She counted their heads.\n"
"\n"
"Thirty seconds. The lizards gave her shield a wide berth. Either they were "
"frightened of this new technology, or... they were waiting her out.\n"
"\n"
"Twenty seconds. She loaded her shotgun.\n"
"\n"
"Ten seconds. The lizards charged - and she hoped she was ready."
msgstr ""

#: .strings.SS2_ITEM_SKATEBOARD_NAME
msgid "Swift Skateboard"
msgstr "Швиткий скейтборд"

#: .strings.SS2_ITEM_SKATEBOARD_DESC
msgid ""
"<style=cIsUtility>Sprint</style> in <style=cIsUtility>any direction</style>. "
"Using a <style=cIsUtility>skill</style> grants a buff which provides "
"<style=cIsUtility>+{0}%</style> <style=cStack>(+{1}% per stack)</style> "
"<style=cIsUtility>movement speed</style> for <style=cIsUtility>{4}</style> "
"seconds, up to <style=cIsUtility>{2}</style> stacks."
msgstr ""

#: .strings.SS2_ITEM_SKATEBOARD_PICKUP
msgid "Sprint in any direction. Using skills makes you move faster."
msgstr ""
"Дає змогу бігти у будь-яку сторону. Використання здібностей прискорює вас."

#: .strings.SS2_ITEM_SKATEBOARD_LORE
msgid ""
"Wheels, rolling against unhewn stone. Unrefined, uncoordinated technique- "
"irresponsible and careless in equal measure.\n"
"\n"
"\"You are doing it wrong.\"\n"
"\n"
"\"I am doing this as I please! This is an art, you know, Brother.\"\n"
"\n"
"\"You've failed countless times already.\"\n"
"\n"
"\"We'll see.\"\n"
"\n"
"Focused eyes, darting as stars reflecting the sky. Lightning flashes against "
"the remote landscape in the distance. Twinkling thunderbolts catching a "
"stray eye. A single lapse of focus, then an impact. A frustrated scoff. "
"Glares, mutual and infuriated, sharp enough to cut through the gap in the "
"air preceding oncoming thunder.\n"
"\n"
"\"I'm beginning to have doubts, Brother.\"\n"
"\n"
"\"..well, I've yet to give up! How could I have failed?\"\n"
"\n"
"Impact, skidding quick enough to sear against the kicked-up dust. Shaky "
"limbs, rising from the ground. Defiance. Potential energy, mounting into "
"heat and purpose, tangible in the air. Suffocating tension, louder than "
"thunder. It all comes crashing down.\n"
"\n"
"\"Another failure.\"\n"
"\n"
"\"..you know, I don't believe I've failed once, Brother. There's something "
"to be said of art about the simple act of learning.\"\n"
"\n"
"\"You HAVE failed! Each and every time you have tried you have failed, and I "
"have attempted to teach you- but you do not listen. I grow tired of teaching "
"and tired of watching!\"\n"
"\n"
"Wheels begin to roll against stone again. They hum and kick like an organ "
"attuned to the pulse of the Earth underfoot, barely holding on.\n"
"\n"
"\"You incessantly add your own additions to even my simplest instructions.."
"\"\n"
"\n"
"Forward movement. The thrill of velocity in one's chest. Of feeling your "
"blood and senses rush back, jostled by inertia. A reminder of truly being "
"alive.\n"
"\n"
"\"When you're done playing with all this, allow me to demonstrate what I've "
"tried to teach.\"\n"
"\n"
"Uncontrollable energy, wild and frenzied- forces converging together at "
"last. A perfect storm.\n"
"Rotation, freed of an axis and speed- that essential rush of heat and "
"velocity.\n"
"Lightning. Raw energy, full of potential- now fully realized.\n"
"Joy and astonishment and elation. Shock. Satisfaction. Excitement. A third "
"voice, calling out impatiently over the Venusian storm.\n"
"\n"
"\"Come in, boys- dinner's ready and it's no weather to be skateboarding in!\""
msgstr ""

