#: .strings.SS2_PYRO_SKIN_DEFAULT
msgctxt ".strings.SS2_PYRO_SKIN_DEFAULT"
msgid "Default"
msgstr "Стандартний"

#: .strings.SS2_PYRO_LORE
msgid ""
"Buzzing, buzzing, and more buzzing. As they tried to go over the final "
"details of the job, the droning of insect wings was the only sound to break "
"through - but it didn’t matter. The job was simple, and he knew how to see "
"it through properly. The woman in the hardhat proceeded back to the port as "
"the man in polymeric fibers equipped a sizable weapon from his back. "
"Clutching it firmly in one hand, he used the other to manage the cargo bay "
"doors, bracing himself for the swarm within.\n"
"\n"
"A suffocating miasma of acid filled the air as the doors slid open. If not "
"for his respirator, the fumes would’ve been unbearable, toxic enough to "
"knock him out within minutes. The thick air was populated with countless "
"giant green bugs, busily flying between corroded containers and the hive "
"structures they’d built between them. Their incessant droning drowned out "
"his thoughts - just the way he liked it. None of the insects took notice of "
"the intruder until a torrent of napalm exploded into a blaze. \n"
"\n"
"Warriors descended as workers scattered, though it was too late for all of "
"them. The ones quick enough to form an offense merely hastened their demise, "
"falling to his feet as the fire devoured them. Napalm clung indiscriminately "
"to nest, pest, and security chest alike as he slowly weaved his way between "
"the labyrinth of cargo that laid out the foundations of the lair. Black "
"smoke began to fill the bay, thickening with each step he took, while the "
"ground piled high with charred remains. More than anything, though, it was "
"the heat - the relentless, searing heat of his cleaning flames - that filled "
"the room. Shipping containers turned into furnaces, and the bay a graveyard "
"as he systematically purged the infestation.\n"
"\n"
"Hours later, little was left but the acrid stench of decay, the occasional "
"mandible or thorax, and a fine layer of ash carpeting the floor. After a "
"third lap around the bay, he finally found what he’d been searching for, "
"stashed away behind cracked container doors in the darkest corner of the "
"room: an unharmed nest of eggs. He chuckled to himself, closing the cracked "
"door and submerging the eggs back into darkness. As the large bay doors "
"slammed shut, the woman in the helmet wrinkled her nose, handing him payment "
"for a job well done. And a job well done it was - one hundred percent of the "
"live bugs reduced to an easy clean-up.\n"
"\n"
"As he left the dock, he thought about the bonus he’d claimed for himself: "
"the eggs, healthily growing in their ideal conditions, where regulation "
"couldn’t look until it was too late. There would never be a job as enjoyable "
"as them."
msgstr ""

